==English==

===Noun phrase===
'''drag bunt'''

#{{baseball}} A ball that has been hit by a [[batter]] who started to run towards first base while holding the bat back over the plate, typically in an attempt to get a [[hit]] rather than to [[sacrifice]]
#: ''Jones fielded the '''drag bunt''', but the runner beat out his throw for a [[single]].''
#{{baseball}} The act of bunting while running towards first base
#: ''The '''drag bunt''' is a skill that few players perfect.''

===Transitive verb phrase===
'''drag bunt'''

#{{baseball}} to [[bunt]] while running towards [[first base]]
#: ''Jones '''drag bunted''' the pitch.''


===Intransitive verb phrase===
'''drag bunt'''

#{{baseball}} to [[bunt]] while running towards [[first base]]
#: ''Smith often '''drag bunts''' if he sees the third baseman playing back.''